{"title_page": "Valeria Zorzetto", "text_new": "{{short description|Italian Paralympic athlete}}\n{{Infobox sportsperson\n| name = Valeria Zorzetto\n| nickname = \n| image = Valeria Zorzetto.jpg\n| imagesize = 240\n| caption = \n| nationality = [[Italia]]n\n| sport = [[Para table tennis]]\n| event = \n| club = H81 Insieme Vicenza Onlus\n| coach = Alessandro Arcigli\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1969|4|21|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Vicenza]], [[Italy]]\n| residence = [[Montecchio Maggiore]], [[Italy]]\n| retired= \n| death_date = \n| death_place = \n| height = \n| weight = \n| pb = \n| country = {{ITA}} \n| medaltemplates =\n{{Medal|Sport|Women's [[para table tennis]]}}\n{{Medal|Country|{{ITA}}}}\n{{Medal|Competition|[[Table tennis at the Summer Paralympics|Paralympic Games]]}}\n{{Medal|Silver|[[2004 Summer Paralympics|2004 Athens]]|[[Table tennis at the 2004 Summer Paralympics \u2013 Women's individual \u2013 Class 4|Individual class 4]]}}\n{{Medal|Competition|[[World Para Table Tennis Championships|World Championships]]}}\n{{Medal|Bronze|2006 Montreaux|Team class 4}}\n}}\n\n'''Valeria Zorzetto''' (born 21 April 1969 in [[Vicenza]]) is an Italian [[Paralympic athletics|paralympic athlete]] that won a medals at the [[2004 Summer Paralympics]].\n\n==Biography==\nDuring her career she has participated in three editions of the [[Paralympic Games]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ipc.infostradasports.com/asp/redirect/ipc.asp?page=athletebio&personid=688871&sportid=-1|title=Zorzetto Valeria|publisher=paralympic.org|accessdate=16 September 2012}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n*[[Italy at the 2012 Summer Paralympics]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IPC athlete|id=valeria-zorzetto|old_id=688871}}\n* [http://londra2012.comitatoparalimpico.it/scheda_atleta.php?id=94 Valeria Zorzetto]{{Dead link|date=May 2019 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }} at [[Comitato Italiano Paralimpico]] {{in lang|it}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Zorzetto, Valeria}}\n[[Category:196