    = 142\n| Viewers         = \n| ShortSummary    = \n| LineColor       = B50000\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 51\n| Title           = I Wand to Bread Free <small>(part 1)</small>\n| AltTitle        = Poteri senza bacchette\n| DirectedBy      = \u00c9ric Gosselet\n| WrittenBy       = \n| Aux2            = \n| OriginalAirDate = \n| AltDate         = {{Start date|2020|4|19}}\n| ProdCode        = 151\n| Viewers         = \n| ShortSummary    = \n| LineColor       = B50000\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 52\n| Title           = I Wand to Bread Free <small>(part 2)</small>\n| AltTitle        = Il processo\n| DirectedBy      = \u00c9ric Gosselet\n| WrittenBy       = \n| Aux2            = \n| OriginalAirDate = \n| AltDate         = {{Start date|2020|4|19}}\n| ProdCode        = 152\n| Viewers         = \n| ShortSummary    = \n| LineColor       = B50000\n}}\n}}\n\n== Production ==\n''Trulli Tales'' is produced by Fandango TV, Congedo CulturArte, and [[Rai Fiction]] in Italy, [[Gaumont Animation]] in France, and Groupe PVP in Canada. Gaumont and Groupe formed a co-production agreement for this series, alongside ''[[Belle and Sebastian (2017 TV series)|Belle and Sebastian]]'' in 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://playbackonline.ca/2015/09/28/groupe-pvp-gaumont-animation-pact-on-two-series/|title=Groupe PVP, Gaumont Animation pact on two series|work=[[Playback (magazine)|Playback]]|publisher=[[Brunico Communications]]|date=September 29, 2015|accessdate=October 12, 2019|first=Julianna|last=Cummins}}</ref> The series was inspired by a book published by Congedo.<ref name=\"italy\">{{Cite web|url=https://allaboutitaly.net/trulli-tales-the-new-disney-cartoon-set-in-alberobello/|title='Trulli Tales', the new Disney cartoon set in Alberobello|date=2018-10-02|website=All About Italy|language=en-US|access-date=2019-02-02}}</ref>\n\nThe show was commissioned by [[The Walt Disney Company]] for its [[Disney Junior]] channels in the [[EMEA]] regions, alongside [[Rai Fiction]] for [[Rai YoYo]] in Italy, [[Ici Radio-Canada T\u00e9l\u00e9]] in Canada, and [[Globosat]]'s [[Globosat#Current networks|Globinho]] in Brazil.<ref>{{cite magazine |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |title=Nicolas Atlan - President of Animation, Gaumont |url=https://issuu.com/worldscreen/docs/tv_kids_guide_2017-2018/20 |magazine=TV Kids |location= |publisher=Worldscreen |date=September 26, 2017 |access-date=October 12, 2019}}</ref> [[Boat Rocker Media]] represents the property for consumer products in the United Kingdom.<ref name=\"toyworld\" />\n\n== Broadcast ==\n''Trulli Tales'' first debuted October 17, 2017 on [[Globosat#Current networks|Gloobinho]] in Brazil.<ref name=uol/><ref name=\"valle\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.quivalleditria.it/en/post/trulli-tales-awarded-and-famous-all-over-the-world/|title=Trulli Tales, awarded and famous all over the world|last=Redazione|date=2018-12-18|website=quivalleditria.it|language=en-US|access-date=2019-02-02}}</ref> The series premiered on December 11, 2017 on [[List of Disney Junior TV channels|Disney Junior]] in Italy,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://bari.repubblica.it/cronaca/2017/11/20/news/trullallero_un_cartone_animato_ambientato_ad-181616854/|title=Trulli Tales, il nuovo cartone per la Disney \u00e8 ambientato ad Alberobello|date=November 20, 2017|accessdate=October 11, 2019|work=[[Animation Magazine]]|lang=Italian}}</ref> and later June 11, 2018 on [[Rai YoYo]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.licensingmagazine.com/2018/06/11/trulli-tales-the-adventures-of-the-trullalleri-on-air-on-tv-from-june-11th-on-rai-yoyo/?lang=en|title=\u201cTRULLI TALES: THE ADVENTURES OF THE TRULLALLERI\u201d ON AIR ON TV FROM JUNE 11TH ON RAI YOYO|date=June 11, 2018|accessdate=October 11, 2019|work=Licensing Magazine}}</ref> In Canada, the series premiered on [[Ici Radio-Canada T\u00e9l\u00e9]] on January 6, 2018,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.pvp.ca/nouvelles/en/2017/12/animated-series-trulli-tales-soon-to-be-broadcast-on-ici-radio-canada/|title=Animated series Trulli Tales soon to be broadcast on ICI Radio-Canada!|date=December 19, 2017|work=Groupe PVP|accessdate=October 11, 2019}}</ref> and on [[Knowledge Network]] on May 7.\n\nOn December 11, 2017, the series debuted across many Disney Junior channels in the [[EMEA]] area, including France and the UK and Ireland. The series also premiered in the latter on [[Tiny Pop]] on January 21, 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/watch/?v=241385163459566|title=One for your diary - brand new Trulli Tales starts 21st January at 4pm!|date=January 18, 2019|accessdate=October 11, 2019|work=[[Tiny Pop]]|publisher=[[Facebook]]}}</ref> In South Africa, the series premiered on February 26, 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cVmSemzkoKo|title=Trulli Tales - NEW SERIES - Starting Monday 26th February @ 18:00!|work=[[Disney Channel (Southern Africa)|Disney Channel]]|publisher=[[YouTube]]|date=February 5, 2018|accessdate=October 11, 2019}}</ref> In Singapore, the series premiered on [[Channel 5 (Singapore)|Channel 5]] on July 15, 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://tv.toggle.sg/en/channel5/shows/trulli-tales/info|title=Trulli Tales Show Info|work=[[Toggle.sg]]|publisher=[[MediaCorp]]|accessdate=October 11, 2019}}</ref> On October 5, the series premiered in the United States on [[Nick Jr.]]<ref name=\"USA\">{{cite web|url=http://nickalive.blogspot.com/2019/10/nick-jr-usa-to-premiere-trulli-tales-on.html|title=Nick Jr. USA to Premiere 'Trulli Tales' on Saturday, October 5, 2019|date=October 4, 2019|accessdate=October 11, 2019|work=NickALive}}</ref> As of November 2019, the series had been sold to 177 territories globally.<ref name=\"Italy Award\"/>\n \n==Merchandise==\n[[Giochi Preziosi]] launched a series of toys for the series in 2018, which were distributed in Italy and the United Kingdom.<ref name=\"toyworld\">{{Cite web|url=https://toyworldmag.co.uk/licensing-news/boat-rocker-to-represent-trulli-tales/|title=Boat Rocker to represent Trulli Tales {{!}} Toy World Magazine|website=toyworldmag.co.uk|access-date=2019-02-02}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hitechweb.info/giochi-preziosi-firma-la-linea-di-giocattoli-su-licenza-trulli-tales/|title=Giochi Preziosi firma la linea di giocattoli su licenza Trulli Tales|date=June 19, 2018|accessdate=November 27, 2019|work=Hitech Web|language=Italian}}</ref> Additional merchandise was produced for Italian release, including educational toys, tissues, stickers, and food products.<ref name=\"toyworld\"/> [[Panini Group|Panini]] began publishing an official magazine in November 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.licensingmagazine.com/2019/11/28/trulli-tales-the-official-magazine/?lang=en|title=TRULLI TALES \u2013 THE OFFICIAL MAGAZINE|date=November 28, 2019|accessdate=November 27, 2019|work=Licensing Magazine}}</ref>\n\n==Awards==\n''Trulli Tales'' was awarded the [[Prix G\u00e9meaux]] for best animated series in 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.licensingmagazine.com/2018/09/20/trulli-tales-awarded-at-the-prix-gemeaux/?lang=en|title=TRULLI TALES AWARDED AT THE PRIX G\u00c9MEAUX|date=September 20, 2018|accessdate=November 27, 2019|work=Licensing Magazine}}</ref> In 2019, it became the first television series to win the Italian Creativity Award from the [[Istituto Italiano di Cultura]] in the United States.<ref name=\"Italy Award\">{{cite web|url=https://www.quotidianodipuglia.it/cultura/trulli_tales_premio_in_america-4874611.html|title=Trulli tales, in America il premio per la creativit\u00e0|first=Claudia|last=Presicce|date=November 20, 2019|accessdate=November 28, 2019|work=Quotidiano Di Puglia|language=Italian}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.trullitales.com/ Official website] {{in lang|it}}\n*{{IMDb title|tt10453700}}\n\n[[Category:2010s Canadian animated television series]]\n[[Category:2010s French animated television series]]\n[[Category:2010s animated television series]]\n[[Category:2017 Canadian television series debuts]]\n[[Category:2017 French television series debuts]]\n[[Category:2017 Italian television series debuts]]\n[[Category:2017 animated television series debuts]]\n[[Category:Canadian flash animated television series]]\n[[Category:Canadian children's animated comedy television series]]\n[[Category:Canadian children's animated fantasy television series]]\n[[Category:Canadian children's animated science fiction television series]]\n[[Category:Canadian preschool education television series]]\n[[Category:Canadian television programs based on children's books]]\n[[Category:French flash animated television series]]\n[[Category:French children's animated comedy television series]]\n[[Category:French children's animated fantasy television series]]\n[[Category:French children's animated science fiction television series]]\n[[Category:French preschool education television series]]\n[[Category:French television programs based on children's books]]\n[[Category:Italian animated television series]]\n[[Category:English-language television programs]]\n[[Category:Disney Channel original programming]]\n[[Category:Disney Junior shows]]\n[[Category:Nick Jr. original programming]]\n[[Category:Nickelodeon shows]]\n[[Category:Rede Globo programmes]]\n[[Category:Television about magic]]\n[[Category:Television series by Boat Rocker Media]]\n", "text_old": "{{Distinguish|Troll Tales}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name            = Trulli Tales\n| image                = Trulli+Tales+logo.png\n| caption              = Official logo featuring the main characters. From left to right: Sun, Ring, Stella, and Zip.\n| show_name_2          = Trulli Tales: The Adventures of Trullalleri\n| genre                = [[Fictional film|Fictional]]<br/>[[Science Fiction]]<br/>[[Action film|Action]]\n| creator              = {{Plainlist|\n* Maria Elena Congedo\n* Fiorella Congedo\n}}\n| based_on             = {{Based on|A book published|Congedo Editore}}<ref name=\"italy\"/>{{specify|date=December 2019}}\n| director             = \u00c9ric Gosselet\n| voices               = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Eleanor Noble]]\n* [[Holly Gauthier-Frankel]]\n* [[Sonja Ball]]\n* [[Richard Dumont]]\n* Jennifer Seguin\n}}\n| theme_music_composer = Alessandro Boriani\n| opentheme            = {{Based on|\"Trulli Tales\"|Sonja Ball, [[Angela Galuppo]], and Eleanor Noble}}\n| endtheme             = \"Trulli Tales\" <small>(instrumental)</small>\n| composer             = {{Plainlist|\n* Alessandro Boriani\n* Fiorella Congedo\n* Maria Elena Congedo\n}}\n| country              = {{ubl|Italy|France|Canada}}\n| language             = English\n| num_seasons          = 1\n| num_episodes         = 52\n| list_episodes        = #Episodes\n| executive_producer   = {{Plainlist|\n* Nicolas Atlan\n* Fiorella Congedo\n* Maria Elena Congedo\n* Domenico Procacci\n* Fran\u00e7ois Trudel\n* Vincent Leroux\n* Michael G. Stern\n}}\n| producer             = {{Plainlist|\n* Marc Dhrami\n* Stefano Basso\n* Fran\u00e7ois Trudel\n* Annita Romanelli\n}}\n| editor               = <!-- Film editors -->\n| runtime              = 11 minutes\n| company              = {{Plainlist|\n* Fandango TV\n* Congedo CulturArte\n* [[Gaumont Animation]]\n* Groupe PVP\n* [[Rai Fiction]]\n}}\n| distributor          = Congedo CulturArte<br>[[Gaumont Animation]]\n| network              = {{ubl|[[Rai Yoyo]] and [[Disney Junior (Italy)|Disney Junior]] (Italy)|[[Disney Junior (French TV channel)|Disney Junior]] (France)|[[Ici Radio-Canada T\u00e9l\u00e9]]|[[Teletoon]] (Canada)}}\n| picture_format       = [[HDTV]] [[1080i]]\n| audio_format         = [[Stereophonic sound|Stereo]]\n| first_run            = Brazil\n| first_aired          = {{Start date|2017|10|17}}\n| last_aired           = {{End date|2019}}\n| website              = https://www.raiyoyo.rai.it/dl/PortaliRai/Programmi/PublishingBlock-844eb8e1-6772-4ebf-b345-3cddc0e103f0.html?ContentItem-1770cbd7-7f0b-4312-bf99-698cfe654128\n| production_website   = <!-- use |production_website_title= to change the display title. -->\n}}\n'''''Trulli Tales''''' ({{IPAc-en|t|r|u\u02d0|l|i\u02d0|\u025b}}), fully known as '''''Trulli Tales: The Adventures of Trullalleri''''', is a Canadian-French-Italian [[Flash animation|flash-animated]] [[children's television series]] created by Maria Elena and Fiorella Congedo. The series first premiered on October 17, 2017 on [[Globosat#Current networks|Globinho]] in Brazil.<ref name=uol>{{cite web|url=https://noticiasdatv.uol.com.br/noticia/bloco-de-notas/nova-estreia-17211|title=Nova estreia|date=October 10, 2017|work=Noticias da TV|first=Daniel|last=Castro|lang=Portuguese}}</ref> The series was produced by Fandango TV, Congedo CulturArte, [[Gaumont Animation]], Groupe PVP, and [[Rai Fiction]].\n\nSet in the fictional world of Trullalleri or Trulliland (which is meant to resemble [[Alberobello]]),<ref name=italy/> the series revolves around four children and one teacher who learn how to cook from their Grandma Trulli's cookbook from the past. But when Copperpot tries to steal it, the four children; Ring, Zip, Stella, and Sun, must stop him with the magical power from their wands.\n\n== Characters ==\n=== Main ===\n* Ring (voiced by [[Eleanor Noble]]) \u2013 The talented leader of the group. He is a generous and kind friend, but can also be a little self-confident and vain. He is good at cooking and is the one in the group who selects the ingredients for each recipe. His wand is a fork and also a magnet, which is able to attract objects. He has brown hair, dark eyes, dressed in red.\n* Zip (voiced by [[Sonja Ball]]) \u2013 The sportsman of the group. He is nice and funny, but sometimes he proves to be moody and impatient. He deals with mincing, blending, and cutting the ingredients selected by Ring. His wand is a kitchen whisk. He has orange hair and green eyes and dressed in blue.\n* Stella (voiced by [[Sonja Ball]]) \u2013 The most vaporous of the group. Although at many times she is quite inattentive, distracted, careless, childish, and naive, she can be good-natured, kind, sensitive, polite, and sweet. She is talented in decorating, as shown by her ability to decorate the dishes. Her wand is a spatula that she uses to decorate the food made by her and her friends. She has brown hair, brown eyes, dressed in yellow.\n* Sun (voiced by [[Holly Gauthier-Frankel]]) \u2013 The first of the group's class. She is very determined, intelligent, and brilliant, but can be touchy and stubborn. She takes care of cooking the dishes in the group. Her wand is a spoon, which she uses to control temperatures. She has blonde hair and blue eyes and is dressed in pink.\n* Miss Frisella - Owner of the Trulli Kingdom bakery and keeper of the Magic Cookbook\n* Trulli Grandma - Creator of the Magic Cookbook and would guide the kids through riddles that would help them solve any of their problems.\n\n=== Villains ===\n* Copperpot (voiced by [[Richard Dumont]]) \u2013 The main villain who always tries to steal the Wizard Chefs' cookbook.\n* Athenina (voiced by Jennifer Seguin) \u2013 Copperpot's employee and pet owl.\n* Rick (voiced By [[Chris Savino]]) \u2013 Copperpot and Athenina's new employee who wants to help at Copperpot to steal the Wizard Chefs' cookbook.\n* Tyler (voiced by [[Sam Register]]) - Cooperpot's That's Mind Wrath Citadel employee\n* Winston (voiced by [[Jay Stephens]]) - Cooperpot's That's Hate on the Felt War employee\n\n=== Recurring ===\n* Teri and Liu - A spider and snail that only appear at the beginning and end of every episode \n* Trulli King - Ruler of TrulliLand\n\n== Episodes ==\n{{Episode table |total_width= |background=#B50000 |overall= |title= |director= |writer= |aux2= |aux2T=Storyboard by |airdate= |airdateT=Italian air date |airdateR=<ref>https://tvprofil.com/it/guida-tv/#!datum=2017-12-11&kanal=disney-junior-it</ref> |altdate= |altdateT=U.S. air date|prodcode= |prodcodeR=<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/showatch/trulli-tales/listings |tit